                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/7—3054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_MATTHEWSHF1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-30T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 30, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>181. Secretary General Foreign Office tells me eighteen countries now firmly
                    committed themselves to support <persName corresp="#p_KLEFFENSEN1">Van
                        Kleffens</persName>. List includes five Latin American, and two Asian
                    countries and several Commonwealth dominions. In addition number of others have
                    indicated probable support but are not formally committed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MATTHEWSHF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Matthews</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
